==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uranin
<hw>U"ra*nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
alkaline salt of fluorescein, obtained as a brownish red substance,
which is used as a dye; -- so called from the peculiar yellowish green
fluorescence (resembling that of <xex>uranium</xex> glass) of its
solutions. See <er>Fluorescein</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uraninite</ent>⟦br⟧
